data.title: Tacoma, Washington, Washington - 3002
data.text:
From Blaine, Washington

Follow I-5 S toward Seattle/Tacoma. Take Exit 137 for WA-99 N toward Fife/Milton. Use the left lane to turn onto Pacific Hwy E. After proceeding through two stop light intersections and just before Willow Rd E, turn right into the parking lot.

From Olympia, Washington

From I-5 N take Exit 136B toward Port of Tacoma. Turn right onto Pacific Hwy E. Proceed past Willow Rd E, then turn left into the parking lot.

Special Instructions

A Service Port is a CBP location that has a full range of cargo processing functions, including inspections, entry, collections, and verification (19 CFR 101.1) Please reference the mailing address location to conduct Service Port related business in person.

After required documents have been uploaded to the Document Image System an email must be sent to the appropriate mailbox. This will greatly reduce confusion and expedite cargo releases.

Special Events:

To get information on upcoming trade events, please request to be added to the Area Port of Seattle Trade distribution by sending an email to Assistant Area Port Director Luca Furnare (LUCA.J.FURNARE@CBP.DHS.GOV)
